{"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Formatting Your Documentation Content","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"DocC"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/daringfireball.net\/projects\/markdown\/syntax","type":"reference"},{"text":", a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lightweight markup language, to give structure and style to your documentation."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"DocC includes a custom dialect of Markdown, documentation markup, which"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"extends Markdown’s syntax to include features like symbol linking, improved","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"image support, term lists, and asides.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To ensure consistent structure and styling, use DocC’s documentation markup for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"all of the documentation you write."}]},{"text":"Add a Page Title and Section Headers","anchor":"Add-a-Page-Title-and-Section-Headers","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a page title, precede the text you want to use with a hash ("},{"code":"#","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"space. For the page title of an article or API collection, use plain text only."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["# Getting Started with Sloths"]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Page titles must be the first line of content in a documentation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"file. One or more empty lines can precede the page title."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the page title of a landing page, enter a symbol link by wrapping the framework’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"module name within a set of double backticks (``)."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# ``SlothCreator``"],"syntax":"markdown"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For a documentation extension file, enter a symbol link by wrapping the path to the symbol","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"within double backticks (``). The path may start with the framework’s module name"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or with the name of a top-level symbol in the module."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows a documentation extension link starting with a framework module name:"}]},{"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# ``SlothCreator\/CareSchedule\/Event``"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example shows a documentation extension link to the same symbol starting with a top-level symbol name:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["# ``CareSchedule\/Event``"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Augment every page title with a short and concise single-sentence abstract or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"summary that provides additional information about the content. Add the summary","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using a new paragraph directly below the page title."}]},{"code":["# Getting Started with Sloths","","Create a sloth and assign personality traits and abilities."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a header for an Overview or a Discussion section, use a double hash"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"code":"##","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and a space, and then include either term in plain text.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["## Overview"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For all other section headers, use a triple hash ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"###"},{"text":") and a space, and then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"add the title of the header in plain text.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["### Create a Sloth"],"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this type of section header in framework landing pages, top-level pages,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"articles, and occasionally in symbol reference pages where you need to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"provide more detail.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Format Text in Bold, Italics, and Code Voice","anchor":"Format-Text-in-Bold-Italics-and-Code-Voice"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"DocC provides three ways to format the text in your documentation. You can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"apply bold or italic styling, or you can use code voice, which renders the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specified text in a monospace font."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add bold styling, wrap the text in a pair of double asterisks ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"**"},{"text":").","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Alternatively, use double underscores (","type":"text"},{"code":"__","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses bold styling for the names of the sloths:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["**Super Sloth**: Likes to eat sticks.","__Silly Sloth__: Prefers twigs for breakfast."],"syntax":"markdown"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use italicized text to introduce new or alternative terms to the reader. To add","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"italic styling, wrap the text in a set of single underscores ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"type":"text","text":") or single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asterisks ("},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses italics for the words "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"metabolism","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"habitat","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["A sloth's _metabolism_ is highly dependent on its *habitat*."],"syntax":"markdown"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use code voice to refer to symbols inline, or to include short code fragments,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as class names or method signatures.  To add code voice, wrap the text in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a set of backticks (`).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the following example, DocC renders the words "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ice"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"fire","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"wind"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lightning"}]},{"text":" in a monospace font:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["If your sloth possesses one of the special powers: `ice`, `fire`, ","`wind`, or `lightning`."],"syntax":"markdown"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To include multiple lines of code, use a code listing instead. For more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"level":3,"text":"Add Code Listings","anchor":"Add-Code-Listings","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC includes support for code listings, or fenced code blocks, which allow you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to go beyond the basic declaration sections you find in symbol reference pages,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and to provide more complete code examples for adopters of your framework. You can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"include code listings in your in-source symbol documentation, in extension"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"files, and in articles and tutorials."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a code listing, start a new paragraph and add three backticks","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(```). Then, directly following the backticks, add the name of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"programming language in lowercase text. Add one or more lines of code, and then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"add a new line and terminate the code listing by adding another three backticks:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["```swift","struct Sightseeing: Activity {","    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {","        sloth.energyLevel -= 10","        return .slow","    }","}","```"]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When formatting your code listing, use spaces to indent lines"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instead of tabs so that DocC preserves the indentation when compiling your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"documentation."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","style":"important"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"DocC uses the programming language you specify to apply the correct syntax","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"color formatting. For the example above, DocC generates the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct Sightseeing: Activity {","    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {","        sloth.energyLevel -= 10","        return .slow","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following table lists the names of the programming languages you can specify","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to enable syntax highlighting for a particular code listing. Each language may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have one or more aliases.","type":"text"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Aliases","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"bash","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"sh, zsh","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"c","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"h"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"cpp"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"cc, c++, h++, hpp, hh, hxx, cxx"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"css","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"diff"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"patch"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"http"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"https"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"java"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"jsp","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"javascript"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"js, jsx, mjs, cjs"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"json","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"llvm"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"markdown"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"md, mkdown, mkd","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"objective-c"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"mm, objc, obj-c, objectivec","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"perl","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pl, pm"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"php","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"python","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"py, gyp, ipython","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ruby"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rb, gemspec, podspec, thor, irb"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"scss","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"shell"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"console, shellsession"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"swift"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"xml"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"html, xhtml, rss, atom, xjb, xsd, xsl, plist, wsf, svg","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Add Bulleted, Numbered, and Term Lists","anchor":"Add-Bulleted-Numbered-and-Term-Lists"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC supports the following list types:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Type"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Usage","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Bulleted list","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Groups items that can appear in any order."}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Numbered list"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Delineates a sequence of events in a particular order."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Term list"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Defines a series of term-definition pairs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t add images or code listings between list items. Bulleted and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"numbered lists must contain two or more items.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a bulleted list, precede each of the list’s items with an asterisk (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"*"},{"text":") and a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"space. Alternatively, use a dash (","type":"text"},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") or a plus sign ("},{"code":"+","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") instead of an asterisk (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"*"},{"text":"); the list markers are interchangeable.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["* Ice","- Fire","* Wind","+ Lightning"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a numbered list, precede each of the list’s items with the number of the step, then a period ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"."},{"text":") and a space.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["1. Give the sloth some food.","2. Take the sloth for a walk.","3. Read the sloth a story.","4. Put the sloth to bed."],"syntax":"markdown"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a term list, precede each term with a dash ("},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"term"},{"type":"text","text":" keyword, and another space. Then add a colon ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":"},{"text":"), a space, and the definition after the term.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["- term Ice: Ice sloths thrive below freezing temperatures.","- term Fire: Fire sloths thrive at boiling temperatures.","- term Wind: Wind sloths thrive at soaring altitudes.","- term Lightning: Lightning sloths thrive in stormy climates."]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A list item’s text, including terms and their definitions, can use the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"style attributes as other text, and include links to other content, including"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"symbols.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Enhance your content’s presentation with special formatting and styling for text and lists."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Structure-and-Formatting","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-tables-of-data","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/other-formatt